        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 9:43PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 943 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 9 miles southwest of Ute Lake State
Park to 5 miles east of Variadero, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tucumcari, Conchas, Conchas Lake State Park, Conchas Dam and
Variadero.

This includes State Road 104 between Mile Markers 48 and 105.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
